    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Season your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully coated</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef</strong> to the dish and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, then remove from the dish and set aside, reserve the dish</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the beef is browning, peel and quarter your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> roughly</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the dish to a medium-high heat and once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>shallot</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 min or until browned</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>red wine paste</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> in 475ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>red wine stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have browned, return the <strong>browned beef </strong>to the dish with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>red wine stock</strong>, <strong>bay</strong> <strong>leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover the dish with a lid and put in the oven for 1 hour or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>beef bourguignon</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has been in the oven for 40 min, reboil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return the potatoes to a low heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013\u00a0this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/beef-bourguignon-with-creamy-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>beef</strong> <strong>bourguignon </strong>over the <strong>creamy mash </strong>and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Discard your <strong>bay</strong> <strong>leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
